# admin/.env.example
# Copy to .env.local (gitignored) and override per environment.
#
# VITE_API_URL — base URL the admin frontend uses for every fetch.
#
# Two ways to wire it:
#
# 1) ABSOLUTE (no proxy). Every request goes cross-origin to the
#    backend. Use this for staging/prod parity or when you want to
#    point the dev build at a deployed backend.
#      VITE_API_URL=https://pagepay.onrender.com/api/v1
#
# 2) RELATIVE (uses the Vite dev-server proxy in vite.config.ts).
#    No CORS in dev because the browser sees same-origin /api calls
#    that the Vite proxy forwards to the local FastAPI server.
#      VITE_API_URL=/api/v1
#
# If unset, the client falls back to the production Render URL
# (`https://pagepay.onrender.com/api/v1`) so the production build
# still works without a .env file.
#
# VITE_API_URL=/api/v1
